309a6f40-52bf-11ea-abf2-8dc9e627a96d	 All Together, works by Holly Graham	-all-together,-works-by-holly-graham	f	[{"end_time": "2020-02-28T00:00:00.000Z", "start_time": "2020-02-27T22:00:00.000Z", "optional_title": ""}]	https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/infinite-industries-event-images/uploads/a10c3d24-6e13-41d0-9c13-31456c0d5c1d.jpg	https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/infinite-industries-event-images/uploads/social/a10c3d24-6e13-41d0-9c13-31456c0d5c1d_social.jpg	637de4f0-d3c3-403a-b57a-8975e242763c	none	400 E College St, Georgetown, KY 40324	me@me.me	\N	An opening reception and artist talk with Holly Graham will take place in the Cochenour Gallery in the LRC on S. Mulberry St. on Thursday February 27, 5-7 PM.	<p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">An opening reception and artist talk with Holly Graham will take place in the Cochenour Gallery in the LRC on S. Mulberry St. on Thursday February 27, 5-7 PM.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">The word “family” for Holly M. Graham has always and continues to represent belonging... a people with which you can be truly yourself and be loved. Her exhibition “All Together” is made of three bodies of work with this focus, which span the last two years. Not everyone experiences the notion of belonging in a typical family setting. Perhaps, one experiences that tender concept with friends who have become a family. In any case, Graham would like her work represented in “All Together” to draw forward that sensation of connection that comes with being a part of an ever-welcoming group.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">Among the three bodies of work represented, “Our Simple Life Illustrated” marks the treasures found in the simple moments of a home. The illustrative fabric series “Family Patterns” utilizes pattern to express individual personalities, while still maintaining the unity of a group, which is represented by the cohesive black line. “Print Takeover” is a light-hearted photographic series experimenting with her family member's expressions, employing the idea of a print leaving it's garment to fill the room, and the feeling with which it might leave the wearer.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">Using both her usual minimalist approach to evoke calm and contentedness, coupled with a new employment of pattern to induce feelings of joy and silliness, Holly Graham invites you to peak inside her daily life as wife and mother.</span></p>	{}			https://www.facebook.com/events/173381397291780/		http://bit.ly/2SCz8su	{}	t	2020-02-19 02:26:09.692+00	2020-02-19 14:10:21.188+00	\N
