d783f5c0-3fb9-11e9-b43e-456ed9f9b823	Will Csorba, Matthew J. Rolin, TBA	will-csorba,-matthew-j.-rolin,-tba	f	[{"end_time": "2019-03-10 00:00:00", "start_time": "2019-03-09 19:00:00", "optional_title": ""}]	https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/infinite-industries-event-images/uploads/4394ed17-a671-4fcd-94b9-2a68381d393d.jpg	https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/infinite-industries-event-images/uploads/social/4394ed17-a671-4fcd-94b9-2a68381d393d_social.jpg	dfef2ffe-0eed-4049-af94-cabf46852417	none	145 Woodland Ave, Lexington, Kentucky 40502	me@me.me	\N	Will Csorba (HOU) - "Will Csorba is a very prolific, young multiinstrumentalist from Houston, TX. He appeared in 2014 and is keeping himself and the community busy since then.	<p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">Will Csorba (HOU) - "Will Csorba is a very prolific, young multiinstrumentalist from Houston, TX. He appeared in 2014 and is keeping himself and the community busy since then.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">Csorba’s main inspiration is the Takoma School of american solo guitar.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">In his music you can hear the virtuosity, the signature picking patterns and historical references of guitarists like John Fahey, Jack Rose or Daniel Bachman.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">Csorba absobs all those influences and produces tracks and projects constantly and he’s good at adapting all kind of styles and techniques."</span></p><p><br></p><p><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4HoJOUTwqpU" target="_blank" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(54, 88, 153);">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4HoJOUTwqpU</a></p><p><a href="https://williamcsorba.bandcamp.com/album/the-cornfields" target="_blank" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(54, 88, 153);">https://williamcsorba.bandcamp.com/album/the-cornfields</a></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">Matthew J. Rolin (CBUS) - "Blue Hole Recordings is proud to present its eighth release, Moment, the second record from guitarist Matthew J. Rolin. With less than a year in Columbus to his name, Rolin has quickly established himself as a fixture on the city’s homespun experimental scene, playing solo and duo sets with Jen Powers (namesake of “I Love You Jen”) in support of Cloud Nothings, Nap Eyes, Amps for Christ, Itasca, Gun Outfit, Charalambides and Nathan Bowles, often at Columbus’ resident laundromat-cum-music venue. Recorded in Rolin’s living room soon after moving to Columbus from Chicago, Moment offers concise thoughts responding to change.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">Rolin’s talent spans instruments: he plays 6- and 12-string guitar on the record, plus a number of “auxiliary instruments”—check the harmonium drone that introduces opener “All That Is Left.” Rolin’s compositions are straightforward and affecting: “4th St at Night” was recorded there, “Heroin” remembers a friend lost to it, “Improv” is just that. But behind the directness lies swirling fingerpicking like a horse’s gallop, textural exploration, 12-string progressions in the vein of Suni McGrath and experimental techniques in the vein of Jack Rose (circa his split with Sylvester Anfang). Rolin features on the latest Imaginational Anthem compilation, curated by Ryley Walker and forthcoming on Tompkins Square; his third record is in the works. Don’t delay."</span></p><p><br></p><p><a href="https://matthewrolin.bandcamp.com/album/moment" target="_blank" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(54, 88, 153);">https://matthewrolin.bandcamp.com/album/moment</a></p>	{}			https://www.facebook.com/events/377058969790261/		http://bit.ly/2NX6gZH	{}	t	2019-03-06 02:45:02.876+00	2019-11-21 13:22:56.034+00	\N
