f21964b0-8109-11e9-b43e-456ed9f9b823	John Harlan Norris: Disintegrants book signing / listening party	john-harlan-norris:-disintegrants-book-signing-/-listening-party	f	[{"end_time": "2019-05-31 20:00:00", "start_time": "2019-05-31 18:00:00", "optional_title": ""}]	https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/infinite-industries-event-images/uploads/a4dbfe8d-227b-4d5c-afb3-59f635470076.jpg	https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/infinite-industries-event-images/uploads/social/a4dbfe8d-227b-4d5c-afb3-59f635470076_social.jpg	d0858cc0-0478-11e8-808e-07b6d0fe568b	none	193 N Limestone, Lexington, KY 40507	me@me.me	\N	Join Institute 193 in celebrating the release of Disintegrants, an art book and full length album by artist and musician John Harlan Norris	<p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">Join Institute 193 in celebrating the release of Disintegrants, an art book and full length album by artist and musician John Harlan Norris. We'll be listening to the Disintegrants Soundtrack, and John will be signing books. You can pre-order your copy (and get $5 off) by clicking below: </span></p><p><br></p><p><a href="https://institute193.bigcartel.com/product/john-harlan-norris-disintegrants" target="_blank" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(56, 88, 152);">https://institute193.bigcartel.com/product/john-harlan-norris-disintegrants</a></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">In Disintegrants, Norris, who exhibited with Institute 193 in 2017, continues his research on portraiture, here motivated by a sense of disembodiment that emerges out of mediated images, digital information, and virtual relationships. As portrait scholar Alba Compo Rosillo points out in her essay 'Metaportraits' included in the book, Norris' paintings 'suggest the presence of selves but do not offer straightforward representations of individuals.' Norris assembles his abstracted compositions from human-made objects like sunglasses, gloves and portable speakers and tools associated with his craft, primarily stretcher bars, to make images that suggest identity as a composite of the signifiers with which we surround ourselves.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">In addition to the paintings, Norris has recorded a full-length album meant to accompany the paintings, titled aptly, Disintegrants Soundtrack, which is included in the book as a CD and digital download.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">About the artist:</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">John Harlan Norris is an artist and musician originally from Nicholasville, KY. His work explores alternative approaches to portraiture and investigates notions such as occupational identity and virtual constructions of the self. Past exhibitions of his work have been held at Institute 193, Trestle Gallery (NY), Egelund Gallery (Denmark), Plus Gallery (CO), 21C Museum Hotel (AR), Jonathan Ferrara Gallery (LA), Greg Thompson Fine Art (AR), Contemporary Arts Center Las Vegas (NV), and David Lusk Gallery (TN) among others. In addition to his solo music projects, Norris records and performs with the group Letters of Acceptance. He lives in Lexington, KY.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">John Harlan Norris: Disintegrants </span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">Softcover, 9 x 12 in. / 62 pages / full color </span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">Pub Date: 2019 </span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">Publisher: Institute 193 </span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">Design and production by Iota Books </span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">ISBN: 978-1-7328482-1-4 </span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">20 USD</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">includes CD and digital download code</span></p>	{}			https://www.facebook.com/events/379317979350734/		http://bit.ly/2QDISlC	{}	t	2019-05-28 05:32:12.795+00	2019-11-21