59a864f0-76bf-11e9-b43e-456ed9f9b823	Fort Maria Screening + Filmmaker/Cast Q&A	fort-maria-screening-+-filmmaker/cast-q&a	f	[{"end_time": "2019-05-20 21:00:00", "start_time": "2019-05-20 19:00:00", "optional_title": ""}]	https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/infinite-industries-event-images/uploads/083f5e00-b530-49e6-9a2c-e089460a09c1.jpg	https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/infinite-industries-event-images/uploads/social/083f5e00-b530-49e6-9a2c-e089460a09c1_social.jpg	446e9860-047a-11e8-808e-07b6d0fe568b	Free	140 E Main St, Lexington, Kentucky 40507	me@me.me	\N	 Cinematic collaboration between writer/director Thomas Southerland and writer/actress Katerina Stoykova	<p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">If you had the pleasure of seeing the first cinematic collaboration between writer/director Thomas Southerland and writer/actress Katerina Stoykova, </span><a href="https://www.facebook.com/proudcitizenthemovie/" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(56, 88, 152); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Proud Citizen</a><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">, then you know what a powerful creative team they are. We are thrilled that they are reuniting in Lexington for a screening of their much-anticipated second collaboration: FORT MARIA.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">Co-Directed by Southerland and S. Cagney Gentry (HARVEST), FORT MARIA is a (mostly) pre-plotted feature-length film with improvised dialogue. In the words of the filmmakers: "Our goal is to create a film that transcends the bonds of formal plotting and characterization to achieve a kind of spontaneous, organic life of its own on screen - to have all the entertaining messiness and tangential humor of real life."</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">Already a festival darling, the film tells the story of Maria--a woman with no country. A Bulgarian immigrant and adoptive mother of a black daughter, she finds herself suddenly stricken with agoraphobia following a break-in at her home in Kentucky. When her daughter’s aging dog dies, Maria’s confinement puts her into equally painful and funny situations that soon entangle her neighbors. As Maria copes with the issues that have led her - a world traveler - into her self-inflicted prison, her daughter Meredith discovers her own identity through a search for her biological family. </span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">"[P]owerful and surprising...full of essential human moments and authentic considerations of race, culture, love, and what truly makes up a family." -- Ashland Independent Film Festival</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">Mr. Southerland and Ms. Stoykova will join us for a Q&amp;A following the film along with other cast and crew.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">This is a free event. Endless thanks to the Lexington Public Library for making this screening possible!</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">Trailer: </span><a href="https://vimeo.com/264359278?fbclid=IwAR0CKQb5-asmQbzlz1kKAAYVsrnDWcxcy51_6w908-aU6xqDzf2HITeerCs" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(56, 88, 152); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">https://vimeo.com/264359278</a></p>	{}			https://www.facebook.com/events/441591259978121/		http://bit.ly/2NV1zPX	{}	t	2019-05-15 03:13:02.656+00	2019-11-21 13:26:59.335+00	\N
