9c102ed0-cd1e-11e9-b43e-456ed9f9b823	Community Reiki and Sound Bath @Centered Lexington! 	community-reiki-and-sound-bath-@centered-lexington!-	f	[{"end_time": "2019-09-06 19:00:00", "start_time": "2019-09-06 14:00:00", "optional_title": ""}]	https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/infinite-industries-event-images/uploads/cf9d0fbe-f1d4-474d-b342-1ddf462270db.jpg	https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/infinite-industries-event-images/uploads/social/cf9d0fbe-f1d4-474d-b342-1ddf462270db_social.jpg	571ab550-cd1b-11e9-b43e-456ed9f9b823	$30 for 20 minute private session	309 N Ashland Ave #180, Lexington, KY 40502, Lexington, 40503, National	kulacameron@gmail.com	\N	Join us from 2-7 PM every Friday for rejuvenating Reiki and Sound Bath combo!	<p>Join Norah and Cameron every Friday at Centered on National avenue for a unique healing combo experience! </p><p><br></p><p>Reiki is the ancient Japanese art of energetic redirection. It is non-invasive, and no touch is required so it is perfect for those with sensitivities to traditional massage. This beautiful practice combined with the deep, healing resonance of Tibetan singing bowls makes for a unique and potentially transformative experience you won't find anywhere else in the region. </p><p><br></p><p>Norah Jones is a licensed Reiki practitioner and yoga instructor. She is highly skilled at the use of Tibetan singing bowls in a theraputic setting. Among her many travels, Norah has studied the healing arts in Thailand, India, Nepal, and a variety of locations around the U.S.</p><p><br></p><p>Cameron Norman is a musician hailing from the steep cliff faces of the Red River Gorge. He plays more than ten different instruments, one of which is the Thai gong. Known for its intense resonant and healing abilities, he became fascinated by the gong's potential in therapy during his near year-long stay in Thailand. </p><p><br></p><p>Please join us! Walk-ins are absolutely welcome, we would be happy for you to join us. Admissions fees can be waived