de552350-cd9a-11e9-b43e-456ed9f9b823	La Pointe Courte	la-pointe-courte	f	[{"end_time": "2019-09-11 21:00:00", "start_time": "2019-09-11 19:00:00", "optional_title": ""}]	https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/infinite-industries-event-images/uploads/4c0188ff-5d0f-49cd-98e1-eaba11fbe9e6.jpg		dbc17929-fa2e-4453-8f31-c3d4e21e14d0	none	214 E Main St, Lexington, KY 40507	me@me.me	\N	SQecial Media is proud to present the first film in this year’s Rosa Goddard International Film Festival	<p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">SQecial Media is proud to present the first film in this year’s Rosa Goddard International Film Festival! In celebration of her ever-questioning, ever-exploring spirit, we have chosen three films by French filmmaker Agnès Varda (1928 – 2019) for this year’s festival. </span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">LA POINTE COURTE (dir. Agnès Varda, 1955)  —  The first film by feminist filmmaker Agnès Varda, this visually stunning masterpiece would provide inspiration for the French New Wave that crested several years later with the early works of Goddard and Truffaut. Part neorealism documentary, part avante-garde meditation on relationship and community, La Pointe Courte follows a man returning to his hometown with his Parisian wife as they explore their marriage and decide whether or not to remain together, all the while navigating the comedies and tragedies of small-town life.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">Tickets cost $5 and will automatically enter attendees in a drawing for prizes before the film. Help us spread the word! The next two films in the festival are CLEO FROM 5 TO 7 (September 18) and FACES PLACES (September 25). All films will show on Wednesday nights at 7pm in the Kentucky Theater. </span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">This is the first time we have focused on a single director. A photographer first, Varda began making films in 1954, having only seen a handful of films herself. Through her fresh perspective and endless experimentation, Varda made extraordinary contributions to modern cinema, photography, and visual art, while championing feminism and human rights in her work and life. She established a career of her own long before it was socially accepted, and raised two children with her husband, fellow French director Jacques Demy, until his death from AIDS in 1990 (during which time she was his primary caregiver). With a career spanning seven decades, Agnès Varda kept working, making films, and challenging expectations until her death this year at the age of ninety, always truly engaged, enraged, and delighted by the world around her.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">Follow SQecial Media or the Rosa Goddard International Film Festival on Facebook for updates:</span></p><p><a href="https://www.facebook.com/sqecialmedia/" target="_blank" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(56, 88, 152);">https://www.facebook.com/sqecialmedia</a></p><p><a href="https://www.facebook.com/rosagoddardfilmfestival/" target="_blank" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(56, 88, 152);">https://www.facebook.com/rosagoddardfilmfestival</a></p>	{}			https://www.facebook.com/events/422855221665516/		http://bit.ly/2KCgHzN	{}	t	2019-09-02 16:01:05.029+00	2019-11-21 13:29:22.811+00	\N
