Corner of Market St and Short St</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">WHY: Affirmation of the Black Lives Matter movement</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">Remarks will be offered by Frank X. Walker, author of 'Loveletter to the World,' from which the phrase Unlearn Fear + Hate originates; Adrian Wallace, Vice President of Lexington NAACP; and Jeff Koonce, WesBanco Market President. Two additional speakers are expected.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">Unlearn Fear + Hate is a community-driven cycle of artworks by Kurt Gohde and Kremena Todorova. Inspired by a need to address growing racial tensions in the United States, the project has promoted public dialog through temporary and permanent activations of the words "Unlearn Fear + Hate," from a commissioned poem by Frank X Walker, Kentucky's first African American Poet Laureate. It is an invitation for everyone to join the work of diminishing the fears we live with by acknowledging our shared humanity.</span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);"> </span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">Major support for the project was from a </span><a href="https://www.facebook.com/NationalEndowmentfortheArts/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(56, 88, 152); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">National Endowment for the Arts</a><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);"> ArtWorks grant, received and administered by </span><a href="https://www.facebook.com/LexArts/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(56, 88, 152); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">LexArts</a><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">. In addition to the NEA grant, funding was supported by the </span><a href="https://www.facebook.com/BGCFKY/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(56, 88, 152); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Blue Grass Community Foundation</a><span style="color: rgb(29, 33,