ikes The Kentucky Theater  Invite  Sarah Madison Brown  Invite Share Details SQecial Media is proud to present the third and final film in this year’s Rosa Goddard International Film Festival	<p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">SQecial Media is proud to present the third and final film in this year’s Rosa Goddard International Film Festival! In celebration of her ever-questioning, ever-exploring spirit, we have chosen three films by French filmmaker Agnès Varda (1928 – 2019) for this year’s festival. </span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">FACES PLACES (Visages Villages) (dir. Agnès Varda &amp; JR, 2017)  —  In her enchanting next-to-last film, we find Varda in documentarian mode (a style of filmmaking she is a master of), joined by portraiturist/muralist/graffiti artist JR. Together they journey through rural France, hearing stories from and creating intimate large format photos of the people they encounter, present and past. Along the way Varda travels through her own past and sets out to find old friend and nemesis Jean-Luc Godard. The film was awarded the L'Œil d'or at the 2017 Cannes Film Festival.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">Tickets cost $5 and will automatically enter attendees in a drawing for prizes before the film. Help us spread the word! All films will show on Wednesday nights at 7pm in the Kentucky Theater. </span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">This is the first time we have focused on a single director. A photographer first, Varda began making films in 1954, having only seen a handful of films herself. Through her fresh perspective and endless experimentation, Varda made extraordinary contributions to modern cinema, photography, and visual art, while championing feminism and human rights in her work and life. She established a career of her own long before it was socially accepted, and raised two children with her husband, fellow French director Jacques Demy, until h