ec0db6d0-d310-11e9-b43e-456ed9f9b823	Cleo from 5 to 7 (presented by Rosa Goddard Int'l Film Festival)	cleo-from-5-to-7-(presented-by-rosa-goddard-int'l-film-festival)	f	[{"end_time": "2019-09-18 21:00:00", "start_time": "2019-09-18 19:00:00", "optional_title": ""}]	https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/infinite-industries-event-images/uploads/ef8a4024-f708-42f1-96c3-f195580af319.jpg	https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/infinite-industries-event-images/uploads/social/ef8a4024-f708-42f1-96c3-f195580af319_social.jpg	dbc17929-fa2e-4453-8f31-c3d4e21e14d0	$5	214 E Main St, Lexington, KY 40507	savannah.wills@uky.edu	\N	SQecial Media is proud to present the second film in this year’s Rosa Goddard International Film Festival! 	<p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">SQecial Media is proud to present the second film in this year’s Rosa Goddard International Film Festival! In celebration of her ever-questioning, ever-exploring spirit, we have chosen three films by French filmmaker Agnès Varda (1928 – 2019) for this year’s festival. </span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">CLEO FROM 5 TO 7 (Cléo de 5 à 7) (dir. Agnès Varda, 1962)  —  Agnès Varda's musings on mortality and human connection are seen through the eyes of pop singer Cleo as she wanders through two hours of a Parisian summer. The film's focus on a complex female lead and its use of city as character makes it a forerunner of films such as Run Lola Run and Frances Ha. Highlights include the film's real-time narrative and the striking black-and-white mise-en-scène (likely a result of Varda's background in photography), and the beautiful full-color tarot spread opening sequence.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">Tickets cost $5 and will automatically enter attendees in a drawing for prizes before the film. Help us spread the word! The next film in the festival is FACES PLACES (September 25). All films will show on Wednesday nights at 7pm in the Kentucky Theater. </span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">This is the first time we have focused on a single director. A photographer first, Varda began making films in 1954, having only seen a handful of films herself. Through her fresh perspective and endless experimentation, Varda made extraordinary contributions to modern cinema, photography, and visual art, while championing feminism and human rights in her work and life. She established a career of her own long before it was socially accepted, and raised two children with her husband, fellow French director Jacques Demy, until his death from AIDS in 1990 (during which time she was his primary caregiver). With a career spanning seven decades, Agnès Varda kept working, making films, and challenging expectations until her death this year at the age of ninety, always truly engaged, enraged, and delighted by the world around her.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">Follow SQecial Media or the Rosa Goddard International Film Festival on Facebook for updates:</span></p><p><a href="https://www.facebook.com/sqecialmedia/" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(56, 88, 152);">https://www.facebook.com/sqecialmedia</a></p><p><a href="https://www.facebook.com/rosagoddardfilmfestival/" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(56, 88, 152);">https://www.facebook.com/rosagoddardfilmfestival</a></p>	{}			https://www.facebook.com/events/365075057727428/		http://bit.ly/37rQYE3	{}	t	2019-09-09 14:48:44.477+00	2019-11-21 13:31:55.995+00	\N
