fcdc7910-af60-11ea-b6c2-ad89bfbe302e	Community Kindness Week	community-kindness-week	f	[{"end_time": "2020-06-16T00:00:00.000Z", "start_time": "2020-06-15T12:00:00.000Z", "optional_title": ""}, {"end_time": "2020-06-20T00:00:00.000Z", "start_time": "2020-06-19T12:00:00.000Z", "optional_title": ""}]	https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/infinite-industries-event-images/uploads/6401b20f-d0f3-4adb-a69e-4fc5d2b85010.jpg		f9adb400-7cef-11ea-9036-6de817efdff1	none	401 West Main Street	me@me.me	\N	Join us June 15 to 19 for a celebration of kindness and empathy through creative, artistic experiences.	<p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">Can art and beauty make the world a better place? We think so! Join us June 15 to 19 for a celebration of kindness and empathy through creative, artistic experiences. </span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">RSVP to the Facebook event for daily posts and project suggestions, along with the opportunity to share YOUR acts of kindness. </span>If you don't have Facebook, no worries. We've outlined the daily themes below and you're welcome to email your ideas and pictures to us!</p><p><br></p><p><strong>MONDAY: Practice Kindness</strong></p><p>Create a Kindness Calendar or Kindness BINGO card with a different act of kindness in each square. Use it as a tool to incorporate intentional kindness into your daily life.</p><p>PBS Kids has a great free&nbsp;downloadable Kindness BINGO&nbsp;card (or just Google "kindness calendar" for lots of great options).<img src="https://ci5.googleusercontent.com/proxy/prjVWi9agcvHo6wWwSY0NoWHiaFTUW1GFE88HIUk5LrHN5aeEIX3D6pJtDlEPNI6Dvf_Ou5XHLexQ1ajT_5sVXHMGfcLsqoinYvkNDmXc8HzvBff2Y637Q=s0-d-e1-ft#https://imgssl.constantcontact.com/letters/images/1101116784221/S.gif" height="1" width="5"></p><p><strong style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">TUESDAY: Speak Kindness</strong></p><p>Our words are powerful. Think about how to use your words to spread kindness. We'll share a few kindness-themed poems and books in the FB event on Tuesday.</p><p>The&nbsp;<a href="https://artcenterky.org/art-box/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(17, 85, 204);"><strong>Art Box</strong></a>&nbsp;project this week is based on the book "<em>The Crayon Box That Talked</em>" - it's a great way to talk with kids about using kind words. Stop by the Art Center starting Tuesday afternoon to grab your FREE supplies to create crayon box puppets!</p><p><strong>WEDNESDAY: Send Kindness</strong></p><p>There are lots of ways to spread kindness and love beyond your immediate circle.</p><p>Create and hide Kindness Rocks to bring a smile to stranger's day. Or Send a card to a loved one in another town.(<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=65e5hKRPEnA" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(17, 85, 204);"><strong>Shaving cream marbling</strong></a>&nbsp;is a virtually foolproof project for creating beautiful cards. Kids of all ages love it!)</p><p>Post your ideas&nbsp;<a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/574428569857871/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(17, 85, 204);">in the FB event</a>!<img src="https://ci5.googleusercontent.com/proxy/prjVWi9agcvHo6wWwSY0NoWHiaFTUW1GFE88HIUk5LrHN5aeEIX3D6pJtDlEPNI6Dvf_Ou5XHLexQ1ajT_5sVXHMGfcLsqoinYvkNDmXc8HzvBff2Y637Q=s0-d-e1-ft#https://imgssl.constantcontact.com/letters/images/1101116784221/S.gif" height="1" width="5"></p><p><strong style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">THURSDAY: Draw Kindness</strong></p><p>What does kindness look like to you? Draw or paint a picture and hang it in your window or on your door to share your vision with your neighborhood. You can also hang your artwork in your home to remind your family to choose kindness.</p><p><strong>FRIDAY: Share Kindness</strong></p><p>Don't keep your creative ideas to yourself!</p><p><br></p><ul><li>Post kindness quotes on your social media channels.</li><li>Chalk an inspirational phrase on the driveway.</li><li>Call your best friend and tell them you love them!</li></ul><p><br></p><p><strong>Kindness Rocks</strong></p><p>Share the love by creating painted Kindness Rocks&nbsp;and hiding them around town. <a href="https://artcenterky.org/visit-us/gift-gallery/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(17, 85, 204); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><strong>Order online</strong></a>&nbsp;and pick up at the Art Center!</p><p>Kit includes 4 smooth rocks, 2 paint brushes, and 6 small containers of paint.</p>	{}			https://www.facebook.com/events/574428569857871/		https://bit.ly/3fprIkQ	{remote}	t	2020-06-15 23:36:09.66+00	2020-06-18 13:09:56.603+00	\N
