a37639f0-43b4-11ea-abf2-8dc9e627a96d	2020 Kentucky Writers Hall of Fame Induction Ceremony	2020-kentucky-writers-hall-of-fame-induction-ceremony	f	[{"end_time": "2020-02-06T01:30:00.000Z", "start_time": "2020-02-06T00:00:00.000Z", "optional_title": ""}]	https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/infinite-industries-event-images/uploads/85333fb1-0443-4a7d-ad5e-f39a16583989.jpg		dbc17929-fa2e-4453-8f31-c3d4e21e14d0	none	214 E Main St, Lexington, KY 40507	kimber@carnegiecenterlex.org	\N	On Wednesday, February 5, 7:00 pm, the eighth class of the Kentucky Writers Hall of Fame will be inducted.	<p>On Wednesday, February 5, 7:00 pm, the eighth class of the Kentucky Writers Hall of Fame will be inducted during a public ceremony at the historic Kentucky Theater in downtown Lexington.</p><p><br></p><p>Cleanth Brooks, Lucy S. Furman, Sam Shepard, and Hollis Summers will join living inductee Sena Jeter Naslund in the incomparable Hall of Fame.</p><p><br></p><p>This year’s ceremony includes a new, occasional award. The Kentucky Literary Impact Award recognizes someone who has made great contributions to the state’s literary culture, but not necessarily as a writer. The first recipient is Gray Zeitz, founder and proprietor of Larkspur Press near the Owen County town of Monterey. For more than 45 years, Zeitz has published elegant, handmade books featuring the work of many of Kentucky’s most important fiction writers and poets.</p><p><br></p><p>Joseph-Beth Booksellers will be on-site to sell books by the inductees, and Naslund will sign books after the ceremony. Kentucky Educational Television will record the ceremony to broadcast at a later date.</p><p><br></p><p>Music will be provided by a string quartet comprised of Benjamin Karp, Dan Mason, Margaret Karp and Tze-Ying Wu. Selections will include music by the Kentucky-born composer Gerald Plain of Louisville.</p><p><br></p><p>Doors will open at 6:00 pm for the event, which is free to the public, and seating will be first come, first ser