ic Hauck has been an entrepreneur of over 30 years leading various types of startups including biotech medical devices to consumer electronics with very successful outcomes for investors. He has served in C-level positions for several mid-size companies including Somfy/Damart a French fortune 500 company in Europe.   He currently serves as Founder and President of MEP Equine Solutions, the developer of a revolutionary fecal egg count system, called “Parasight” currently being commercialized. </span><a href="https://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.parasightsystem.com%2F%3Ffbclid%3DIwAR2mhjt_a831fbizsEFEC2ii75ohBmJBEHJx4jL2B9F5D7S1h10SRfBe9qE&amp;h=AT1Zbt-1ZccIBJtPSOagRD50UyCT9goSAFs7tO9HyEJGPQnmOuvVJ7iMRJg1DuarKbOijCGFFW5elQuK47yyNLqmFLJ7V_OHLRVX5ZTuQWGucsjpS_aV4p3cCdo2OrTKTjjQJRjiVyw92OAc0aiEWSWZ6g" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(56, 88, 152);">www.parasightsystem.com</a></p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(29, 33, 41);">Eric is an angel investor with the Bluegrass Angels located in Lexington KY. Eric also serves as an Adjunct Professor at the University of Kentucky’s Gatton Business College where he teaches a Capstone MBA course for entrepreneurs. Additionally, He serves as a Board member in several companies including two health science start-ups and one turnaround located in the KY area. Eric holds a BA in Biochemistry from the University of Arizona and an MBA and MS in Science and Technology Commercialization from Northeastern University located in Boston MA.  He is the proud father of 4, is happily married to his wife Barbie, and loves to race cars when he has time.  </span></p>	{}			https://www.facebook.com/events/365141344410951/		https://bit.ly/3cTQZT8	{remote}	t	2020-04-28 00:52:05.444+00	2020-04-29 01:32:32.245+00	\N
