c2662400-f7b0-11ea-a43d-dfe2af8cac81	Once Vacant: Bodies in motion... still	once-vacant:-bodies-in-motion...-still	f	[{"end_time": "2020-10-18T01:00:00.000Z", "start_time": "2020-10-18T00:00:00.000Z", "optional_title": ""}, {"end_time": "2020-10-18T02:30:00.000Z", "start_time": "2020-10-18T01:30:00.000Z", "optional_title": ""}]	https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/infinite-industries-event-images/uploads/979799e7-3e20-4880-a824-aac8d57a1e47.jpg		ad6120f0-f7b0-11ea-a43d-dfe2af8cac81	$15 per car, proceeds benefit the University of Kentucky Big Blue Pantry 	1540 University Drive	me@me.me	\N	The University of Kentucky Department of Theatre and Dance presents Once Vacant: Bodies in motion…still.	<p>The University of Kentucky Department of Theatre and Dance presents&nbsp;<strong><em>Once Vacant: Bodies in motion</em>…<em>still.&nbsp;</em></strong>The dancers will perform in the Orange parking lot on UK's campus, while the audience will maintain social distance surrounding the performers in their cars.</p><p>The practice of occupying vacant spaces is a tool that many dancers and dance companies are accessing globally to continue to create, perform, and advance the field of dance during the pandemic. As dancers and choreographers, we continue to seek motion as a means of enlivening a world that has become motionless.<em>&nbsp;Once Vacant</em>&nbsp;reimagines a public space while illuminating the vital role that dance can play in advancing political, social and cultural discussions. Choreographers Susie Thiel, Stephanie Harris and Theresa Bautista's dance works center around the questions, what does the body mean in spaces and places and how can entropy lead to liberation?</p><p><br></p><p><strong>Admission for this performance is <em>per car</em> not per person. One ticket admits one vehicle. Please remain in your vehicle during the performance. <em>*All proceeds will to go the University of Kentucky Big Blue Pantry resource to help combat the affects of food insecurity among